{"source_key":"sha256-f88bd5c54ac5fbbfc982c6d403b2565f","record_index":520,"record_hash":"sha256:9f598964ed68906eba0e0e440a869e580ba558413fadd0191db9085c5757639a","timestamp":"2026-05-24T14:45:31.226Z","kind":"tool_call","source_event_kind":"codex:response_item:custom_tool_call","role":null,"text":null,"tool_name":"apply_patch","tool_input":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Update File: /Users/kiril/Documents/tars/Tars/02 Active/agent-session-capture/agent-trail.md\n@@\n ## Privacy And Publication\n \n Agent Trail is more sensitive than local handoff because it is meant to be\n opened by colleagues.\n \n-Before publishing or linking:\n+For public v1, Agent Trail treats a publicly fetchable `refs/meta/main` as\n+already published metadata. On-demand URL replacement does not grant access to\n+private data; it only renders a review page from metadata that is fetchable\n+without credentials.\n+\n+There is no Forge-specific public redaction pass in v1. That makes\n+`but-agentlog`'s public/read projection load-bearing. Forge must only render\n+records returned by that projection; it must not read or render raw internal\n+records directly.\n+\n+The rendered data must preserve these `but-agentlog` guarantees:\n \n - records must be redacted\n - local filesystem paths should not be exposed\n - raw provider session ids should not be exposed\n - hidden/system/developer prompts should not be exposed\n - source records should stay bounded and redacted\n - the user should understand that the trail may contain prompts and tool output\n \n-The first product design needs an explicit publication boundary. Capturing data\n-into GitMeta does not automatically mean every pull request should expose a\n-public or team-visible Agent Trail.\n+If the required `but-agentlog` public/read projection does not exist yet, build\n+that before rendering Agent Trail pages from Forge.\n+\n+Public v1 snapshots should be public but not promoted. Serve them with\n+`noindex` until the publication model is more mature.\n*** End Patch\n","source_record":{"timestamp":"2026-05-24T14:45:31.226Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"custom_tool_call","status":"completed","call_id":"[REDACTED:entropy]","name":"apply_patch"}}}